â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ ğŸ“ get-or-create-tracking-id/
â”‚   â”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ ğŸ“„ index.ts
â”‚   â”‚   â”‚       Purpose: Supabase Edge Function to retrieve an existing `tracking_pixel_id` for an `email_setup` record, or generate, save, and return a new UUID if one doesn't exist.
â”‚   â”‚   â”‚       Details:
â”‚   â”‚   â”‚         - Accepts `emailSetupId` (the primary ID of the `email_setups` row) in the request body.
â”‚   â”‚   â”‚         - Fetches the `email_setups` record.
â”‚   â”‚   â”‚         - If `tracking_pixel_id` field is already populated, it returns that ID.
â”‚   â”‚   â”‚         - If `tracking_pixel_id` is NULL, it generates a new UUID using `crypto.randomUUID()`.
â”‚   â”‚   â”‚         - Updates the corresponding `email_setups` row, setting the `tracking_pixel_id` to the new UUID.
â”‚   â”‚   â”‚         - Returns the (either existing or newly created) `trackingPixelId`.
â”‚   â”‚   â”‚         - Uses the shared Supabase admin client and CORS headers. Includes `@ts-ignore` for Deno-specific imports to satisfy local linters.
â”‚   â”‚   â”‚       Input: `{ "emailSetupId": "uuid" }`
â”‚   â”‚   â”‚       Output: `{ "trackingPixelId": "uuid" }` or an error object.
â”‚   â”‚   â”‚       Usage: Called by the frontend (e.g., `WebsiteTrackingPage.tsx`) to ensure a persistent and unique ID is available for generating the website tracking pixel script.
