â”œâ”€â”€ ğŸ“ contexts/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ ğŸ“„ DnsStatusContext.tsx
â”‚   â”‚   Purpose: Manages and provides global state related to DNS verification status and the DNS configuration modal.
â”‚   â”‚   Details:
â”‚   â”‚     - Exports `DnsStatusProvider` and `useDnsStatus` hook.
â”‚   â”‚     - Manages state for:
â”‚   â”‚       - `overallDnsStatus`: ('pending' | 'partially_verified' | 'verified' | 'failed_to_verify' | null) - Current overall DNS status.
â”‚   â”‚       - `isDnsModalOpenGlobally`: (boolean) - Controls visibility of the global `DnsConfigurationModal`.
â”‚   â”‚       - `selectedDnsProvider`: (object | null) - The DNS provider object selected by the user (from `DNS_PROVIDER_DISPLAY_OPTIONS`).
â”‚   â”‚       - `dnsContextLoaded`: (boolean) - Indicates if the initial DNS status has been loaded.
â”‚   â”‚     - Provides functions:
â”‚   â”‚       - `setOverallDnsStatus`: Updates `overallDnsStatus`.
â”‚   â”‚       - `showDnsModal(provider?)`: Sets `isDnsModalOpenGlobally` to true and updates `selectedDnsProvider`. If no provider is passed and none is already selected, defaults to "other".
â”‚   â”‚       - `hideDnsModal()`: Sets `isDnsModalOpenGlobally` to false.
â”‚   â”‚       - `setSelectedDnsProvider`: Updates `selectedDnsProvider`.
â”‚   â”‚       - `setDnsContextLoaded`: Updates `dnsContextLoaded`.
â”‚   â”‚   Usage: `DnsStatusProvider` wraps relevant parts of the application (likely in `App.tsx`). Components like `GlobalDnsNotificationBar`, `DnsConfirmationPage`, and `MainContentWithGlobalModal` (in `App.tsx`) use the `useDnsStatus` hook to access and modify this shared state.
â”‚   â”‚
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ ğŸ“„ LoadingContext.tsx
â”‚   â”‚   Purpose: Manages and provides global state for showing/hiding a loading screen.
â”‚   â”‚   Details:
â”‚   â”‚     - Exports `LoadingProvider` and `useLoading` hook.
â”‚   â”‚     - Manages an `isLoading` boolean state.
â”‚   â”‚     - Provides `showLoading()` and `hideLoading()` functions to toggle the state.
â”‚   â”‚   Usage: `LoadingProvider` should wrap the application (e.g., in `App.tsx`). Components can use `useLoading` to trigger the loading screen.
â”‚   â”‚
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ ğŸ“„ DnsStatusContext.tsx
â”‚       Purpose: Manages and provides global state related to DNS verification status and the DNS configuration modal.
â”‚       Details:
â”‚         - Exports `DnsStatusProvider` and `useDnsStatus` hook.
â”‚         - Manages state for:
â”‚           - `overallDnsStatus`: ('pending' | 'partially_verified' | 'verified' | 'failed_to_verify' | null) - Current overall DNS status.
â”‚           - `isDnsModalOpenGlobally`: (boolean) - Controls visibility of the global `DnsConfigurationModal`.
â”‚           - `selectedDnsProvider`: (object | null) - The DNS provider object selected by the user (from `DNS_PROVIDER_DISPLAY_OPTIONS`).
â”‚           - `dnsContextLoaded`: (boolean) - Indicates if the initial DNS status has been loaded.
â”‚         - Provides functions:
â”‚           - `setOverallDnsStatus`: Updates `overallDnsStatus`.
â”‚           - `showDnsModal(provider?)`: Sets `isDnsModalOpenGlobally` to true and updates `selectedDnsProvider`. If no provider is passed and none is already selected, defaults to "other".
â”‚           - `hideDnsModal()`: Sets `isDnsModalOpenGlobally` to false.
â”‚           - `setSelectedDnsProvider`: Updates `selectedDnsProvider`.
â”‚           - `setDnsContextLoaded`: Updates `dnsContextLoaded`.
â”‚       Usage: `DnsStatusProvider` wraps relevant parts of the application. Components use `useDnsStatus` hook.
