â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ ğŸ“„ DnsConfirmationPage.tsx
â”‚   â”‚   Purpose: Guides the user through adding DNS records to their domain provider and allows interaction with a global DNS configuration modal.
â”‚   â”‚   Details:
â”‚   â”‚     - Uses the shared `@/components/Navbar`.
â”‚   â”‚     - Fetches `email_setups` data (domain, `website_provider`, `dns_provider_name`, DNS records values, statuses) for the authenticated user.
â”‚   â”‚     - Calls `get-domain-provider` Supabase edge function for auto-detection.
â”‚   â”‚     - Displays a grid of clickable cards for DNS providers (from `DNS_PROVIDER_DISPLAY_OPTIONS`). Highlights provider based on `website_provider`, auto-detected `dns_provider_name`, or `selectedDnsProvider` from `DnsStatusContext`.
â”‚   â”‚     - Clicking a provider card calls `showDnsModal(provider)` from `DnsStatusContext` to open the global `DnsConfigurationModal`.
â”‚   â”‚     - **Auto-opens modal**: If `selectedDnsProvider` is set in context on page load (e.g., from notification bar click), the modal opens automatically for that provider.
â”‚   â”‚     - **No longer displays overall DNS status directly** (handled by global notification bar).
â”‚   â”‚     - **No longer renders its own modal instance.**
â”‚   â”‚     - Retains local `handleVerifyDns` function, but this is for the page's own verification logic if any is reinstated; the global modal uses its own verification logic defined in `App.tsx`.
â”‚   â”‚     - "Previous" button navigates to `/info-clarification`.
â”‚   â”‚     - "Next Step" button navigates to `/website-tracking`. Button is enabled even if DNS is not fully verified, showing a toast warning instead.
â”‚   â”‚     - Uses `lucide-react` icons. Jungle-themed styling.
â”‚   â”‚   Usage: Step in the multi-step onboarding flow. Interacts with `DnsStatusContext` and implicitly relies on `DnsConfigurationModal` being rendered globally by `App.tsx`.
